Mr. Kamalodine joined B. Riley & Co. in 2004 as an equity analyst covering special situations and transitioned to the company’s investment banking department in 2008 to lead the creation of its public issuer advisory group.  He is now primarily focused on the structuring, negotiation and execution of a variety of transactions, including private and public financings of both debt and equity, merger and acquisition assignments, valuation studies and fairness opinions.
Mr. Kamalodine has a successful track record of working with emerging growth and both private and public middle market companies to enhance shareholder value through various corporate finance initiatives. His experience includes engagements in the semiconductor, Internet software and services, and industrial manufacturing industries. 
Mr. Kamalodine received a B.S. degree in Financial Economics from the University of Southern California and an M.B.A from the Wharton School.
