John Ahn is President of B. Riley & Co. and Head of Corporate Finance. Mr. Ahn joined B. Riley in 2004 and has wide range of experience in capital raising, trading, and sales of distressed debt and equities. 
From 2003-2004, he was a Managing Director in the high yield and distressed bond group at Maxcor Financial Group. Earlier, Mr. Ahn was a loan trader at Security Pacific Bank in Los Angeles in the Loan Syndications group.  Mr. Ahn also was a Partner at Standard Capital Group in Los Angeles, an investment-banking firm that specialized in capital raising for middle market companies.
Mr. Ahn attended Williams College and earned his Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics.
