Greg Presson
Senior Managing Director

.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address) 949-250-5500  Newport Beach, CA 

vCard
|.(JavaScript must be enabled to view this email address) |View Bio 

Mr. Presson joined B. Riley & Co. in 2003 as Senior Managing Director as part of the firm’s merger with L.H. Friend, Weinress, Frankson & Presson, an Irvine-based investment bank and securities broker-dealer.  Mr. Presson began his financial services career in 1980 as a Vice President of Corporate Finance with Emmett A. Larkin & Company, a San Francisco based private investment bank. From 1982 to 1992, he co-founded Cruttenden & Company, an Irvine based investment bank, and served as the firm’s Senior Managing Director and head of its Corporate Finance practice. From 1992 to 2003, Greg  served as Senior Managing Partner and head of Corporate Finance for L.H. Friend, Weinress, Frankson & Presson, LLC.

Mr. Presson has an extensive track record of working with emerging growth and middle market companies to enhance shareholder value through the creation of strategic and corporate finance initiatives. He has served as a financial advisor on dozens of successful engagements including: SDC Technologies, Jimsair Aviation, VXI Technologies, Nupla Corporation, Level Studios, Etreby Computer Company, Trojan Battery Company,  Discovery Partners International, Motion Engineering, Gregg Gift Company, Magnetek, Pro-Log, Rand Technologies, American Recreation Centers, The Kinetics Group, Athens Corporation, Zoltek Companies, Micro Technology, Future Domain, Richmond Technology, Endar Corporation and Molecular Simulations.  In addition, Mr. Presson has completed successful corporate sales to high profile public corporations such as: Mitsui Chemicals, IBM, Motorola, Digital Equipment Corporation, U.S. Filter, Enesco, Adaptec, American Manufacturing and Foundry (AMF), Prime Medical and Automated Data Processing (ADP). He is currently a member of the Board of Directors of Delta Financial, J.F. Weiss & Company, The Santa Ana Country Club and the Get-A-Grip Foundation.

Mr. Presson received a B.S. degree in Economics from California State University, Long Beach.
